cost or earn the community.

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:12.020
HATSUE KATAYAMA:
[SPEAKING JAPANESE]

00:03:25.550 --> 00:03:27.870
NARRATOR: The town has
what's known as a [JAPANESE]

00:03:27.870 --> 00:03:31.290
shop, meaning circular, were
residents can bring in and take

00:03:31.290 --> 00:03:33.320
used items for free.

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:36.020
There's also a factory where
local women make products out

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:37.280
of discarded items.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:39.830
AKIRA SAKANO: We have
lots of old kimonos

00:03:39.830 --> 00:03:43.770
or old clothes or these
flags not used anymore.

00:03:43.770 --> 00:03:46.380
So we asked all these
grannies, who really

00:03:46.380 --> 00:03:48.020
had the skills for the sewing.

00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:52.060
Then they made it into a craft
like teddy bears or bags,

00:03:52.060 --> 00:03:54.120
or what I'm wearing
right now, as well.

00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:56.630
It's made out of
all these fish flags

00:03:56.630 --> 00:04:01.370
that we celebrate and use
for the Children's Day.

00:04:01.370 --> 00:04:03.360
NARRATOR: Businesses
all over Kamikatsu

00:04:03.360 --> 00:04:06.620
have incorporated ways
to become zero waste.

00:04:06.620 --> 00:04:10.650
AKIRA SAKANO: We are cutting,
by doing the recycling, the cost

00:04:10.650 --> 00:04:15.410
into one third compared to when
we actually burned everything.

00:04:15.410 --> 00:04:20.149
We are trying to focus more, and
totally change our lifestyles,

00:04:20.149 --> 00:04:22.190
to not to produce any waste.

00:04:22.190 --> 00:04:26.690
Even in this small town
with only 1,700 people,

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:28.100
everyone looks up to each other.

00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:30.470
And they look after and
take care of each other.

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:31.905
So this kind of
supporting system

00:04:31.905 --> 00:04:34.450
that was in the
community really helped

00:04:34.450 --> 00:04:36.300
for the implementation
of the zero waste.

